#reflection.hidden
    .ui.container#reflection-read(style="width: 90%;")
        .ui.stackable.middle.aligned.grid
            .column.nine.wide.computer.only.sixteen.wide.tablet.only
                h1.ui.header.large#learn-title
                    .content
                        i.lightbulb.icon
                        | Reflect

                p Take a moment to think about the following:
                .ui.bulleted.list
                    .item(style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.65rem; margin-bottom: 10px") Have you ever used email for communication or keeping in touch with friends and family? If yes, what has been your experience with it? If not, do you now feel comfortable exploring this method of communication? 
                    .item(style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.65rem;") Based on what you've learned about identifying potential scams, how do you plan to manage your emails?
                .ui.centered.grid
                    img.ui.small.image(src=`${public_resources}/images/shared_sources/reflection.svg`)

            .column.seven.wide.computer.only.sixteen.wide.tablet.only
                //- button.ui.big.blue.button(onclick="toggleReflection()") Journal thoughts
                .type-here
                    .ui.form
                        .ui.fluid.left.corner.labeled.input(style="font-size: 1.25rem;")
                            .ui.left.corner.label(style="font-size: 1rem;")
                                i.pencil.alternate.icon
                            textarea(placeholder="Type your thoughts here. What you input will not be saved or shared with anyone.")

